The dynamic equilibrium equation for moderate rotational speeds neglecting Coriolis effect is derived from Lagrange’s equation of motion and global form equation is expressed as,19
(11)[M]{δ··}+([K]+[Kσ]){δ}={F(Ω2)}+{F}
where {F(Ω2)} is nodal equivalent centrifugal forces and {δ} is global displacement vector. Geometric stiffness [Kσ] depends on initial stress distribution and is obtained by iterative procedure upon solving,20
(12)([K]+[Kσ]){δ}={F(Ω2)}
